    <h4>About FBO.gov</h4>
    <p>FBO.gov or Federal Business Opportunities (FedBizOpps) is where you can find procurement opportunities for the Federal government. Government users post details of opportunities at FBO.gov. Vendors can search for particular opportunities that suit their criteria and then apply for those. Government users can then award an opportunity to a particular vendor at FBO.gov.</p>

    <p>Every business day, over 2,000 opportunities are posted on FBO.gov.  Each of these opportunities contains a Classification Code, Procurement Type, and Set-Aside Code. By down-selecting these values on teamFBO, you will only be presented with leads that match your team's area of expertise.</p>

    <p><a name="teams"></a></p>
    <br><br>
    <hr>
    <h4>Teams</h4>
    <p>A team is a private entity where members can evaluate opportunities that match the team's opportunity evaluation criteria. The evaluation criteria is defined by the Team Lead.</p>

    <p>On the <%= link_to "Team", team_members_path %> tab, you can view other team members. You may also view high level information about <%= link_to "other teams", teams_path %>, but cannot access detailed information. </p>

    <p><a name="roles"></a></p>
    <br><br>
    <hr>
    <h4>Roles</h4>
    <p>Roles determine what you are allowed to do on teamFBO. Team Leads can set selection criteria, define a team's charter, and add new people to the team. Evaluators can put opportunities on the "Watchlist" and comment on why a particular lead seems compelling.</p>

