    <p><a name="criteria"></a></p>
    <br><br>
    <hr>
    <h4>Selection Criteria</h4>
    <p>Opportunities featured on FBO.gov contain a Classification Code, Procurement Type, and Set-Aside Code. By down-selecting these values on teamFBO, you will only be presented with leads that match your team's area of expertise.</p>
    <p>Team Leads may define selection criteria. Your team's selection criteria is <%= link_to "here", team_path(current_user.team) %>.</p>
    <div class="alert">
      <strong>Warning!</strong> Selection Criteria changes only look forward. If a Team Lead changes criteria, prior opportunities will not be evaluated with the new criteria.
    </div>

    <p><a name="evaluate"></a></p>
    <br><br>
    <hr>
    <h4>Evaluate Opportunities</h4>
    <p>Opportunities are classified by <%= link_to "Not Evaluated", opportunities_path(:set_filter => 1) %>, <%= link_to "Watchlist", opportunities_path(:set_filter => 2) %>, and <%= link_to "Reject", opportunities_path(:set_filter => 3) %>. </p>

    <p>New opportunities that match your team's criteria are placed in the "Not Evaluated" state.  If a team member thinks the opportunity may be a fit, s/he may add the opportunity to the watchlist.  Comments may also be added as to why the opportunity is a good one.</p>

    <p>Other team members may comment on the opportunity. Or, if the opportunity is not a match, it may be rejected. It is best practice to add a comment when rejecting an opportunity. </p>

    <p>Rejects provide important information for your team. Team members can learn why the lead is not an appropriate match. Leads can use this information to fine tune selection criteria.</p>

